## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent data and the inherent biases in opinion pieces. The perspectives gathered are primarily from Western legal systems, which may not fully represent global views on jury trials. Additionally, the complexity of legal systems means that the effectiveness of jury trials can vary significantly depending on jurisdiction and specific legal contexts. Further empirical research is needed to assess the impact of potential reforms or alternatives to jury trials.